<p>Pakistan and Afghanistan agreed to a 48-hour ceasefire following a week of deadly cross-border fighting, with the pause taking effect late Wednesday at 6:00 pm in Islamabad [france24.com#1][newarab.com#1][pbs.org#1]. The truce comes after officials and local reports said dozens of troops and civilians were killed in recent days, including at least 12 Afghans in border fighting and separate explosions in Kabul that killed at least five and wounded 35 before the ceasefire took hold [nytimes.com#1][newarab.com#1]. Islamabad accuses Kabul of allowing militants to stage attacks from Afghan territory, a claim Afghan authorities deny [france24.com#1][newarab.com#1]. Afghanistan’s Taliban government said it has ordered its forces to honor the pause, &quot;unless it is violated,&quot; while Pakistan’s foreign ministry said both sides will strive for a constructive solution through dialogue [newarab.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/Mw92Z3Z0hZ1wFlDTxspSsQgUvsYtGoZ64TzB9qWd-Ctis6haCZfCUbZCI56XEsyhwNM0tw__CpMWJUgXZmFqZV5DUF-y6THxMJvjEhb5eddqx2SG7Odb-JU21s4xaVZzuBhPsfL_Gtw_JeuXsVMAckWNb0p2lgCnxE2sfkkcdn04wKPlJzW9qDcEo0cB8_TvKF3-DvoPHuxnT5ZLYE2mpIJynDDdrKqhIPmdKyguW4s' alt='Taliban guards near the border with Pakistan as fighting flared around Spin Boldak before the ceasefire.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Who requested truce: Each side asserted the other asked for the 48-hour pause, underscoring strained trust between the neighbors [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Where fighting flared: Clashes continued Wednesday in the Spin Boldak border area of southern Afghanistan and in central Pakistan before the truce began [nytimes.com#1].</li><li>Kabul explosions: Two evening blasts in Kabul killed at least five and wounded 35; a Taliban spokesman cited an oil tanker and a generator, without linking them to the border clashes [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Militant safe havens: Pakistan alleges militants use Afghan soil to plan attacks, a charge Kabul denies amid the broader dispute over cross-border security [france24.com#1][newarab.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Unless it is violated - Zabihullah Mujahid</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Pakistan Ministry of Foreign Affairs: During the ceasefire period, both sides will seek a positive solution through constructive dialogue. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/ceasefire-called-after-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Afghanistan’s Taliban government: Ordered the army to respect the truce, with the caveat it would respond if the agreement is violated. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/ceasefire-called-after-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Pakistan government: Accuses Kabul of providing safe haven to militants who plan assaults from Afghan territory. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251016-ceasefire-called-after-new-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>FRANCE 24</a>)</li><li>Afghan authorities: Deny harboring Pakistani Taliban militants amid the uptick in border tensions. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/ceasefire-called-after-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>The New Arab</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/show/news-wrap-pakistan-and-afghanistan-agree-to-a-48-hour-ceasefire-after-days-of-clashes'>News Wrap: Pakistan and Afghanistan agree to a 48-hour ceasefire after days of clashes</a> - pbs.org</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251016-ceasefire-called-after-new-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>Ceasefire called after new Pakistan-Afghanistan clashes kill dozens</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/ceasefire-called-after-pakistan-afghanistan-clashes-kill-dozens'>Ceasefire called after Pakistan-Afghanistan clashes kill dozens</a> - newarab.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/15/world/asia/clashes-afghanistan-pakistan.html'>Afghanistan and Pakistan Announce Cease-Fi